    <header class="header">
      <h1>Canyon Pass Open House Process</h1>
      <p>Complete walkthrough and application guide</p>
      <div class="effective-date">Effective August 7, 2025</div>
    </header>

    <main class="content">
      <section class="section">
        <h2 class="section-title">üìã Process Overview</h2>
        <div class="timeline">
          <div class="timeline-step">
            <div class="timeline-number">1</div>
            <strong>Submit application</strong>
            <span>Submit 3 to 5 business days in advance</span>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-step">
            <div class="timeline-number">2</div>
            <strong>Receive approval</strong>
            <span>Confirmation sent by management</span>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-step">
            <div class="timeline-number">3</div>
            <strong>Hold open house</strong>
            <span>Weekends only, 8 AM to 6 PM</span>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-step">
            <div class="timeline-number">4</div>
            <strong>Close out</strong>
            <span>Remove signage and return visitor materials</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2 class="section-title">üìú Official Policy</h2>
        <div class="policy-box">
          <h3>Open House Policy</h3>
          <p>
            Open houses are permitted within Canyon Pass when the following requirements are met.
          </p>
          <ol class="policy-list">
            <li>
              Submit a request to
              <a href="mailto:Yolanda.quiroz@associaarizona.com">Yolanda.quiroz@associaarizona.com</a>
              with the property address, map or directions, open house date and time, and day-of contact phone number
              at least 3 to 5 business days before the event.
            </li>
            <li>
              One temporary industry standard open house sign is allowed at the property while the realtor or
              representative is on site. Signs may be displayed only between 8 AM and 6 PM on Saturdays and Sundays.
            </li>
            <li>
              Up to three directional signs are allowed per property to guide visitors. These must be placed only with
              the permission of the property owner.
            </li>
            <li>
              Signs may not be placed on community common areas including entrances, medians, or sidewalks.
            </li>
            <li>
              All signs and related materials must be removed immediately after the open house concludes.
            </li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2 class="section-title">üìù Open House Request Form</h2>
        <div class="form-section">
          <form id="openHouseForm" novalidate>
            <div class="form-group">
